[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering testing structure issues**\n\nI'm pondering whether checkstyle requires public test methods since existing ones might be package-private. I noticed an issue with assertThat(...).isOne() — does it actually exist? I remember AssertJ has methods like isZero, isOne, and isPositive. Hm, I think the AfterEach method only resets after the test, not before, which could be problematic if a test fails. Maybe BeforeEach would help, especially since test order is random. Oh, and I should note the potential problem with closing PrintStream in appender.stop. I wonder how this affects test order!\n\n**Improving output stream management**\n\nI need to think about whether running the same test class multiple times in the same JVM could cause issues with parameters. To ensure robustness, I could make AnsiConsole create new PrintStreams upon reset, since the fields are not final. Resetting and reassigning would prevent closing the previous stream from impacting the next execution. If the appender holds the output stream after stopping, that’s a problem. I should ensure methods like outStream() return the current one, making ByteArray and PrintStream mutable instead. Time to edit my approach!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0a05747ff7814e5b0169f7176bbcdc8196b6e8cc24c6e309c5\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9xdyNeOGcRRINAUEZwQ-g84Qm3uLDmsVn92HmeevdYKzuFGMCk7PwWEeGCuLHnjWRVDYJdyRc3BV61e7iFq5xy3x4PbajNLvGcPyXRrH7WEO-WXJP_kPiGDaP5sjqu-IgdkK1DICiKddr4nJjRn-dCt5omrajc-pJA5ctUwhFL5PI0cq9glYS2Tl3p8CE7x-gxGMQWH46YQnEgje3zY68Brff4CSvYWTUaZd3PGoH7TW_0SYmzh2Gazh6G5gSxHmzBRWbAKP4fPWKN9U1xGk4JcsvaHlqVZ0xwbzE1XZfyGirG8DOXztD7UzMVE0qE09y0UkmGPlpEM6Vvf_hf05deST-iSzOBd9-0W3ZL7vpMDEdBDmotuc7zHxB7Tn7tbcQUWFRm_XWVhtujG1aTxhQZp2CUYgHnuQ1hjlOoWJ-TKh5wPyu3ZeLZ72JjDMErNx2ksLoTMoPskypcCnFsXmUqTj4DVtWbQj4-wdR4NGG4B_Xr_Z4Ai0mb9rRZrMvF6tD-mXadAX8ekFpymEXiKl8hkG2P5